* 1.5KE18A TVS Diode SPICE Model
* Unidirectional Transient Voltage Suppressor
* Datasheet parameters:
*   Vrwm (standoff) = 15.3V
*   Vbr (min/max) = 17.1V / 18.9V (test current 1mA)
*   Vc (clamping) = 29.2V at Ipp = 76.5A (8/20us pulse)
*   Vc = 24.4V at Ipp = 1A
*   Ppk = 1500W
*
* Pin convention:
*   PLUS  = protected positive rail (cathode band side of the physical part)
*   MINUS = ground reference (anode side of the physical part)
*
* Usage: X_tvs rail_node gnd_node TVS_1_5KE18A
*   In normal operation both internal diodes are reverse biased.
*   During overvoltage, D_tvs reverse-breaks down at Bv=18V to clamp.

.subckt TVS_1_5KE18A PLUS MINUS

* Both diodes oriented anode=MINUS, cathode=PLUS (reverse biased when PLUS > MINUS).
* D_fwd: a conventional diode; blocks in normal polarity, conducts if rail goes negative.
D_fwd MINUS PLUS D_FWD_MDL
.model D_FWD_MDL D(Is=1e-12 N=1.05 Rs=0.01 Bv=100 Ibv=1m)

* D_tvs: the clamping element; reverse-breaks down at Bv = 18V.
D_tvs MINUS PLUS D_TVS_MDL
.model D_TVS_MDL D(Is=1e-14 N=1.05 Rs=0.15 Bv=18.0 Ibv=1m
+  Cjo=2000p M=0.33 Vj=0.7)

.ends TVS_1_5KE18A
